pullRequest.title: [Node Mgr] Support Bulk Node Registration and Fix Upload API
pullRequest.bodyText:
This PR proposes the following two changes:

Add a new bulk create API to support batch node registration
Fix the current Upload API to support uploading a json file with multiple nodes. More context as follows.

Context
The Node Mgr API /nodes/upload doesn't meet the design goal of registering multiple nodes in one shot. The required format of machine.json file is as follows:
{
   "Hosts": [
      {
         "local_ip": "10.213.43.01",
         "node_id": "cc09465c-5ed6-400e-806d-fbe3d12f94a9",
         "mac_address": "00:A0:C9:14:C8:29",
         "node_name": "Compute1",
         "server_port": 50001,
         "veth": "eth0"
      },
      {
         "local_ip": "10.213.43.02",
         "node_id": "a976fe8a-2ebc-4d8b-9750-a6ec31b9680e",
         "mac_address": "00:A0:C9:14:C8:3A",
         "node_name": "Compute2",
         "server_port": 50001,
         "veth": "eth0"
      },
      ......
      {
         "local_ip": "10.213.43.19",
         "node_id": "7fa7f9b8-8ce5-4c61-9a09-a739eeb965ac",
         "mac_address": "00:A0:C9:14:C8:4F",
         "node_name": "Compute19",
         "server_port": 50001,
         "veth": "eth0"
      }
   ]
}

nodes.bodyText: Why do we want to throw an exception about "empty file" here?
The bulk creation chooses a key "host_infos", which is different from the /upload API, it is for our own benefits to choose the same key for both APIs, either "host_infos" or "Hosts".
Can you add a UT to cover the new /bulk/nodes API? Also, the /upload appears to be problematic. It will be nice to fix them all together.

Could you please check API name?  "/bulk/nodes"? or "/nodes/bulk"
API naming convention was:
/module_name (e.g. "nodes" for node manage")/api_name ("bulk")

Assertion to ensure the same size is necessary.
We also need to check other fields, including the key and value.
